# Backend

## API routes (`src/app/api/`)

- REST-ish JSON; consistent `{ data }` / `{ error: { code, message } }` shape
- Auth: read session from Supabase server client; reject unauthenticated requests
- AuthZ: verify `org_id` membership before any org-scoped operation
- Validate request body with Zod schemas in `src/lib/validations/`

## Server Actions

- Use for form mutations from Server/Client Components
- Always revalidate affected paths after writes
- Return `{ success, error? }` — never throw to the client for expected failures

## Supabase clients

| Client | Use |
|--------|-----|
| `lib/supabase/server.ts` | Server Components, Actions, API routes |
| `lib/supabase/client.ts` | Browser auth only |
| Service role | Inngest jobs / admin scripts only — never expose to client |

## Long-running work

- AI generation and PPTX export run via Inngest, not inline in request handlers
- Update `decks.status` and `exports.status` atomically
- Log failures to Sentry; store error on row for user visibility

## Rules

- Parameterized Supabase queries only; no string-built SQL
- Idempotent webhook handlers (Stripe, Inngest)
- Rate-limit AI and export endpoints per org
